com.opengamma.strata.engine.marketdata

Interface MarketDataLookup

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BaseMarketData

    public interface MarketDataLookup
    A interface for looking up items of market data by ID, used when building market data.

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • containsValue

        boolean containsValue(MarketDataId<?> id)
        Checks if this set of data contains a value for the specified ID and it is of the expected type.
        Parameters:
        id - an ID identifying an item of market data
        Returns:
        true if this set of data contains a value for the specified ID and it is of the expected type

      • containsValues

        default boolean containsValues(Set<? extends MarketDataId<?>> ids)
        Checks if this set of data contains values for all the specified IDs with the expected types.
        Parameters:
        ids - IDs of items of market data
        Returns:
        true if this set of market data contains values for every ID and the values have the expected types

      • getValue

        <T> T getValue(MarketDataId<T> id)
        Returns a market data value.

        The date of the market data is the same as the valuation date of the calculations.

        Type Parameters:
        T - type of the market data
        Parameters:
        id - ID of the market data
        Returns:
        a market data value
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if there is no value for the specified ID

      • getValues

        default Map<MarketDataId<?>,Object> getValues(Set<? extends MarketDataId<?>> ids)
        Returns a map of market data values for a set of IDs.

        The return value is guaranteed to contain a value for every ID. If any values are unavailable this method throws IllegalArgumentException.

        Parameters:
        ids - market data IDs
        Returns:
        a map of market data values for the IDs
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if there is no value for any of the IDs

      • getObservableValues

        default Map<ObservableId,Double> getObservableValues(Set<? extends ObservableId> ids)
        Returns a map of observable market data values for a set of IDs.

        The return value is guaranteed to contain a value for every ID. If any values are unavailable this method throws IllegalArgumentException.

        Parameters:
        ids - market data IDs
        Returns:
        a map of market data values for the IDs
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if there is no value for any of the IDs
